<div class="row">
  <div class="col-lg-7 order-2 order-lg-1">
    <section>
      <h5>Canvas</h5>

      <p>The <var>canvas</var> component renders the <var>div</var> that contains the map. Usage of the <var>canvas</var> is <b>optional</b> and the examples will rarely use it because a canvas is created for you by default. If you do call the canvas component, then the default canvas will not be rendered.</p>

      <p>You can use the <var>canvas</var> to add extra classes or control the order of components within the map context. For example, if you are rendering an <var>autocomplete</var> input, you might want it to appear above the map canvas. Calling the <var>canvas</var> explicitly after that input ensures the correct ordering without having to resort to styling hacks.</p>

      <CodeSnippet @name="basic-canvas.hbs" />
    </section>

    <LinkToNext @nextPage={{this.nextPage}} />
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-5 order-1 order-md-2">
    <GMap
      @lat={{this.london.lat}}
      @lng={{this.london.lng}}
      @zoom={{12}}
      @styles={{this.primaryMapStyle}} as |g|>

      <input
        type="text"
        class="form-control input-lg mb-3"
        aria-label="I’m an element that needs to be above the map."
        placeholder="I need to be above the map!">

      <g.canvas class="ember-google-map-responsive" />

      <g.marker @lat={{this.london.lat}} @lng={{this.london.lng}} />

      <input
        type="text"
        class="form-control input-lg mt-3"
        aria-label="I’m an element that needs to be below the map."
        placeholder="I need to be below the map!">

    </GMap>
  </div>
</div>